===Etymology 1===
From French [[apostrophe#French|apostrophe]], or Latin [[apostrophus]], from Greek [[αποστροφος]] ‘accent of elision’, a noun use of an adjective from [[αποστρεφειν]] ‘turn away’.

====Noun====
{{en-noun|apostrophe|apostrophes}}

# The text character '''’''', which is used to mark the possessive case ('s) or to show omission of letters or numbers (tho', they'll, '65).

